SIMPLE: stupid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stupid
<hw>Stu"pid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stupidus</ets>, fr. <ets>stupere</ets> to be stupefied: cf. F.
<ets>stupide</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very dull; insensible;
senseless; wanting in understanding; heavy; sluggish; in a state of
stupor; -- said of persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O that men . . . should be so <qex>stupid</qex> grown . . . ⟦br⟧
As to forsake the living God!</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With wild surprise,⟦br⟧
A moment <qex>stupid</qex>, motionless he stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resulting from, or evincing, stupidity; formed
without skill or genius; dull; heavy; -- said of things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Observe what loads of <qex>stupid</qex> rhymes⟦br⟧
Oppress us in corrupted times.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Simple; insensible; sluggish; senseless; doltish;
sottish; dull; heavy; clodpated.</syn> -- <wordforms><wf>Stu"pid*ly</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Stu"pid*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stupidity</ent>⟦br⟧
